encodePublicKey

public byte[] encodePublicKey(java.security.PublicKey key)

Returns the encoded form of the designated SRP public key according to the Raw format supported by this library.

The Raw format for an SRP public key, in this implementation, is a byte sequence consisting of the following:

  1. 4-byte magic consisting of the value of the literal Registry.MAGIC_RAW_SRP_PUBLIC_KEY,
  3. 1-byte version consisting of the constant: 0x01,
  4. 4-byte count of following bytes representing the SRP parameter N in internet order,
  5. n-bytes representation of a BigInteger obtained by invoking the toByteArray() method on the SRP parameter N,
  6. 4-byte count of following bytes representing the SRP parameter g,
  7. n-bytes representation of a BigInteger obtained by invoking the toByteArray() method on the SRP parameter g,
  8. 4-byte count of following bytes representing the SRP parameter y,
  9. n-bytes representation of a BigInteger obtained by invoking the toByteArray() method on the SRP parameter y,

Specified by:
encodePublicKey in interface IKeyPairCodec
Parameters:
key - the key to encode.
Returns:
the Raw format encoding of the designated key.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the designated key is not an SRP one.

encodePrivateKey

public byte[] encodePrivateKey(java.security.PrivateKey key)

Returns the encoded form of the designated SRP private key according to the Raw format supported by this library.

The Raw format for an SRP private key, in this implementation, is a byte sequence consisting of the following:

  1. 4-byte magic consisting of the value of the literal Registry.MAGIC_RAW_SRP_PRIVATE_KEY,
  3. 1-byte version consisting of the constant: 0x01,
  4. 4-byte count of following bytes representing the SRP parameter N in internet order,
  5. n-bytes representation of a BigInteger obtained by invoking the toByteArray() method on the SRP parameter N,
  6. 4-byte count of following bytes representing the SRP parameter g,
  7. n-bytes representation of a BigInteger obtained by invoking the toByteArray() method on the SRP parameter g,
  8. 4-byte count of following bytes representing the SRP parameter x,
  9. n-bytes representation of a BigInteger obtained by invoking the toByteArray() method on the SRP parameter x,
  10. one byte which indicates whether the SRP parameter v is included in this encoding (value 0x01) or not (value 0x00).
  11. 4-byte count of following bytes representing the SRP parameter v,
  12. n-bytes representation of a BigInteger obtained by invoking the toByteArray() method on the SRP parameter v,

Specified by:
encodePrivateKey in interface IKeyPairCodec
Parameters:
key - the key to encode.
Returns:
the Raw format encoding of the designated key.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the designated key is not an SRP one.
